Entoloma cyanomelaenum

possesses larger (9–11 × 5.5–6.5 μm) spores and its pileus turns red in KOH (
Boedijn 1929
; 
Horak 1980
); 

E. gainsvillae

has slightly larger spores (8–10 × 6–7 μm) and a smooth pileus (
Murrill 1943
; 
